						<p>
							When you have been injured on the job and the Defense Base Act applies, you may think that getting compensated for your injuries is a simple matter. However, there are several steps that must be followed or your claim can be delayed or even denied. Not only this, but your employer’s DBA insurance carrier may challenge the severity of your injuries or question whether they are even “work-related.”
						</p>
						 
						<p>
							Rather than risk a delay or denial of your claim, it is advisable to seek the assistance of an experienced Defense Base Act attorney who can advocate forcefully on your behalf. A DBA claim lawyer can help you navigate the often-complex laws and regulations that govern these claims and can help you receive the compensation you deserve for your overseas workplace injuries.
						</p>
 
						

